The paper deals with data structures for representing binary relations, which is a fundamental concept in computer science. The paper proposes several novel binary relation representations that are space-efficient and support a wide range of queries. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with data representation problems, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper also proposes representations that support machine learning and artificial intelligence applications, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also deals with reductions among operations, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes efficient algorithms for supporting a large subset of queries, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
